
# Introduction

For my first year Computer Science module on Object Oriented Programming, a java program was commissioned for QUB's fictitious photography department to construct a program (using Eclipse) for managing a collection of 10+ images across various genres, used to create albums for display purposes.

## Features

- Five utility classes for image metadata, image album, image manager, genre enumeration, and a console-based menu.
- An application class integrating menu and image manager instances.
- Capable of interaction with and managing images from specific albums (in this case, the Images folder).

